  "title" : "How to show all parents and subclasses of a class in IntelliJ IDEA?",
  "body" : "<p>When I'm editing a Java class in Eclipse, when my cursor is over a class variable, I can do <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>T</kbd> to have a popup that shows all its parents and subclasses. What is the equivalent in IntelliJ?</p>\n\n<p>Example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Use|r user = new User();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The pipe is my cursor.</p>\n"
